{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-configure-and-design-product-labels-in-magento-2/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to configure and design Product Labels in Magento 2","content":"\n<p>New stores may confuse customers to navigate through the site with the new options available, and because of this product search proce ss will become longer. Therefore, Product labeling is a crucial aspect of e-commerce as it helps to effectively communicate information about the product to potential customers. To make it easier, you can <a href=\"/how-to-create-configurable-product-in-magento-2/\">create configurable product in Magento 2</a> which will allow customers to easily choose the desired product options.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In <a href=\"https://business.adobe.com/in/products/magento/open-source.html\">Magento 2</a>, an open-source e-commerce platform, creating and configuring product labels is made easy with its user-friendly interface and features. This blog will guide you through the process of <strong><em>how to configure and design Product Labels in Magento 2.</em></strong></p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Steps to Configure and Design Product Labels in Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Enable Product Labels</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step to creating product labels in Magento 2 is to enable them. To do this, navigate to the Magento 2 backend and go to Stores > Configuration > Catalog > Product Label. In the Product Label section, set the “Enabled” option to “Yes.” This will enable the product labels in your Magento 2 store.</p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained  inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:420px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src