534ac024487cf3250/d548986b8a7b5ca755a0cc9dc0dacc1c/how-to-configure-and-design-product-labels-in-magento-2-4.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2Fhow-to-configure-and-design-product-labels-in-magento-2-4.png&a=w%3D282%26h%3D178%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&cd=2023-03-17T06%3A00%3A10 282w\",\"sizes\":\"(min-width: 282px) 282px, 100vw\"}},\"layout\":\"constrained\",\"width\":282,\"height\":178},\"alt\":\"\",\"className\":\" inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\",\"data-wp-inline-image\":\"5\"}</script></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 6: Save and Apply Label</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The final step is to save the label and apply it to a product. To apply the label, go to Catalog &gt; Products in the Magento 2 backend. In the Products section, select the product you want to apply the label to and click on the “Edit” button. In the Product Information section, select the label from the “Product Label” dropdown and save the product. The label will now be displayed on the product page.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Conclusion:</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Product labeling is a crucial aspect of e-commerce as it helps to effectively communicate information about the product to potential customers. Magento 2 makes it easy to create and configure product labels with its user-friendly interface and features. By following the steps outlined in this blog, you can set up and design product labels in Magento 2 with ease.</p>\n<div class='sfsi_Sicons sfsi_Sicons_position_left' style='float: none; vertical-align: middle; text-align:left'><div style='margin:0px 8px 0px 0px; line-height: 24px'><span>Please follow and like us:</span></div><div class='sfsi_socialwpr'><div class='sf_fb_share sf_icon' style='text-align:left;vertical-align: middle;'><a  target='_blank' rel='noopener' href='https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=/how-to-configure-and-design-product-labels-in-magento-2/' style='display:inline-block;'><img class='sfsi_wicon'  data-pin-nopi